discussion.content:
I think the question has something wrong, that the User 1 should be in Group 1.

In this case, the answer should be NO YES NO.

User 1 cannot access from Device 1, as User 1 is not in Group 2, so blocked by Policy 2;
User 2 can access from Device 1, as Device 1 is compliant which excluded from Policy 1, and User 2 is in Group 2 which is excluded from Policy 2, and meet Policy 3 as User 2 is in Group 1;
User 2 cannot access from Device 2, as Device 2 is not compliant which is blocked by Policy 1.
